results.longDescription: Season six begins with the Confederation losing the war. The Jem'Hadar ship crashes, leaving Dax injured and under the care of Dr. Bashir in "Rocks and Shoals." Sisko has been promoted and Dax is put in command of the Defiant during "Behind the Lines." In "Change of Heart," Worf must decide between the life of his wife Jadzia, and the success of his mission. Other episode that standout include "Profit and Lace," in which Quark's relationship with Rom's mother, Ishka, convinces Grand Nagus Zek to allow equal rights for women. "The Sound of Her Voice" left the Defiant trying to save Captain Lisa Cusak and in the episode "Tears of the Prophets," Sisko has been ordered to launch attacks against Cardassia and the Dominion.
